collectible.name: Red-Crowned Crane
collectible.description:
Wearables created by Yumika

The rare crane was said to be nearly extinct,
but it was saved thanks to the pristine environment of the Kushiro Marsh.
In 1952, the marsh was designated as a special natural monument and accomodated only a dozen red-crowned cranes.
Today, the number has increased to 1,000, and during the winter, red-crowned cranes can be seen close to human settlements in the area in search of food.
